Sasaern spewed a jet of fire, igniting a small patch of forest. The tall Slacker then circled above it, observing the timing. Curiously, as he slowed down, the strange screams behind him also ceased. Sasaern had forgotten that he still had a passenger on his back.
"Please, Tenuk, you've transformed into a Slacker before!"
"Flying yourself and being suddenly dragged away by a huge pink dragon are two different things!"
"How's it going, Kayer?"
Clearly, Kayer did not agree with Nishi's statement. He looked paler than usual, and his claws were deeply embedded in Sasaern's back, drawing blood from the Slacker. But Sasaern clearly didn't care. Still, Sasaern realized he had scared his new friend and landed on an open area.
"Sorry sorry, I smelled something. I need to deal with it!"
"Do you have to drag us along too?" Tenuk climbed off Sasaern's back, slid down along the tail, and asked sharply, "We left Revertik behind! We abandoned that big, tough guy! How will he find us?"
"He'll figure it out... " Nishi clicked his tongue. "Revertik might be slow, but he's not stupid."
"Does Revertik know how to drive?"
Nishi blinked and turned to look at Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Revertik drive? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive anything as cute as Kayer's little car. He only started riding in cars to work because you always drove us to work."
A laugh interrupted them. Sasaern suddenly burst out laughing, but no one knew what he was laughing at. It took Sasaern a while to calm down.
"Sorry sorry, I just imagined your big armored friend riding a specially designed bicycle for children named Temsen. That scene was so hilarious! I wish I could read minds. This idea is too interesting! I must keep it safe!"
Kayer also laughed because he could imagine what Sasaern was thinking. "Okay, okay. But what did you smell? Why are you flying so fast?"
Sasaern grunted, took off, and soon disappeared. Then he flew back and dropped a corpse in front of Nishi. It was an Orozarak, a very rare golden-white dragon species. But its head was gone. "Another one dead. I heard their cries. Smelled their blood. I must protect them, hunt the killer. This is Ishini's command. Those creatures are nearby."
The powerful Slacker suddenly froze. Nishi and Kayer also froze, their attention drawn to a gap at the edge of the open space. A huge and black entity was staring at them, hissing. It spread its two pairs of massive wings and rushed forward, its target set on Sasaern, completely ignoring the three small ones in its way. Kayer and Tenuk barely managed to sidestep, but Nishi found himself dragged down, nearly thrown onto Sasaern.
Sasaern grabbed Nishi with its long and dexterous tail and flung her onto its back, then took off. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly caught up.
Kayer clicked his tongue, drew a rifle from behind, and opened his bag to take out a bullet belt. He hung the belt around his chest for easy access, but soon realized that Nishi, Sasaern, and the monster were nowhere to be seen.
"Hey, Tenuk, can you transform into a flying animal?" Kayer asked.
"Do you want to follow them?"
"Rubbish."
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"So what? I have a powerful rifle in my hands, ready to fire at any moment. All I need to do is see it, and I can bring it down."
Tenuk hesitated for a moment, then took a step back to give himself some space. With a low, somewhat painful groan, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turning into scales, and his arms transforming into wings. He quickly became a regular light blue Slacker, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Tenuk now looks like a typical Slacker, with neatly arranged scales on his back and a pair of spines that make it easier for Kayer to grab him. It took Tenuk a long time to take off, but once airborne, he quickly adjusted his course and tried to catch up.
However, Tenuk and Kayer soon realized they were not facing just one opponent. A second dark monster emerged from beneath them, and Tenuk barely avoided colliding with it.
"I guess this is the other terrifying big monster Raneeks was worried about?" Kayer frowned, attempting to shoot at the second monster but missing, as he quickly reloaded.
Tenuk didn't respond; he was busy flying towards Nishi and Sasaern, even though the other monster was chasing them. Kayer clumsily turned around to face the monster. The monster was pursuing them, which Kayer saw as good news because it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two bullets pierced through the monster’s upper wing, causing it to howl in pain before disappearing into the woods. Kayer wasn't sure if it was still following them, but he felt it wouldn't be able to keep up anymore.
Ahead, Sasaern was wildly swinging his body, spraying flames at the black monster, while Nishi clung desperately to Sasaern to prevent him from falling. Although the monster was surely injured, it seemed enraged and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs didn't appear to do much damage. After stabilizing himself, Sasaern gave Nishi an opportunity to draw her weapon—a trusted shotgun. Naturally, a shotgun wouldn't work against such a monster, but the scattered bullets might at least scare off this black beast?
